---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Doctor of Business Administration (DBA) | Brenkley Doctoral College" description="Brenkley Doctoral College's DBA programme — three years part-time for senior professionals. Original research, expert supervision, flexible delivery. £8,500 per year.">

  <section class="bg-surface border-b border-border py-16 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <p class="section-label mb-4">Programme</p>
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-4">Doctor of Business Administration</h1>
      <p class="text-xl text-accent font-medium mb-4">DBA &mdash; Three years part-time &mdash; £8,500 per year</p>
      <p class="text-lg text-muted max-w-2xl">The Brenkley Doctoral College DBA is the highest level of professional doctoral education for business and management practitioners. Over three years, you conduct rigorous original research in your own professional context — generating knowledge that is both academically credible and practically significant.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Overview -->
  <section class="py-16 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6 mb-12">
        <div class="card text-center">
          <div class="text-2xl font-bold text-accent mb-2">3 Years</div>
          <p class="text-sm text-muted">Part-time, structured around your professional schedule</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card text-center">
          <div class="text-2xl font-bold text-accent mb-2">£8,500/yr</div>
          <p class="text-sm text-muted">Total £25,500. Payment plans available. Employer sponsorship welcome.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card text-center">
          <div class="text-2xl font-bold text-accent mb-2">Online + Residential</div>
          <p class="text-sm text-muted">Online learning platform plus two residential weekends per year</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-12">
        <div>
          <p class="section-label mb-3">Who It's For</p>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Is the DBA Right for You?</h2>
          <p class="text-muted mb-4">The DBA is designed for senior professionals with substantial management experience who want to use doctoral research to investigate a significant challenge or question in their field. It is not an MBA with a research component — it is a full doctoral degree requiring original contribution to knowledge.</p>
          <p class="text-muted mb-4">You are likely a good fit for the DBA if you are a senior manager, director, or executive with at least five years of leadership experience; you have a Master's degree at Merit or above (or equivalent professional qualification); and you have a research question or area of professional interest that you have been wanting to investigate rigorously for some time.</p>
          <ul class="text-muted text-sm space-y-2 list-disc list-inside">
            <li>Senior professional with 5+ years management experience</li>
            <li>Master's degree at Merit or Distinction (or Level 7 equivalent)</li>
            <li>Clear research interest in a management or business topic</li>
            <li>Committed to 15–20 hours of study per week</li>
            <li>Supported by employer or able to self-fund</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div>
          <p class="section-label mb-3">Entry Requirements</p>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">What We Look For</h2>
          <div class="space-y-4">
            <div class="card">
              <h3 class="font-semibold mb-1">Academic Qualifications</h3>
              <p class="text-muted text-sm">Master's degree at Merit or Distinction, or equivalent Level 7 professional qualification. Applications from candidates with strong professional portfolios but without a Master's may be considered for the Access to Doctorate pathway.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="card">
              <h3 class="font-semibold mb-1">Professional Experience</h3>
              <p class="text-muted text-sm">Minimum five years of senior professional experience in management, leadership, or a relevant professional field. Your professional context will be the environment in which your research is conducted.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="card">
              <h3 class="font-semibold mb-1">Research Proposal</h3>
              <p class="text-muted text-sm">A preliminary research proposal of 1,500–2,000 words, setting out your proposed research area, its significance, and an initial sense of your methodological approach. This is refined through supervision in Year 1.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Structure -->
  <section class="bg-surface border-y border-border py-16 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
      <p class="section-label mb-3">Programme Structure</p>
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-8">Three Years to Doctorate</h2>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
        <div class="card">
          <div class="text-xl font-bold text-accent mb-3">Year 1</div>
          <h3 class="font-semibold mb-3">Foundation &amp; Design</h3>
          <ul class="text-muted text-sm space-y-2">
            <li>Research Foundations module (philosophical frameworks, research paradigms)</li>
            <li>Research Design and Methodology module</li>
            <li>Literature Review development</li>
            <li>Research proposal development and approval</li>
            <li>Ethics application submission</li>
            <li>Monthly supervision meetings</li>
            <li>Two residential weekends (cohort-based)</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <div class="text-xl font-bold text-accent mb-3">Year 2</div>
          <h3 class="font-semibold mb-3">Data Collection &amp; Analysis</h3>
          <ul class="text-muted text-sm space-y-2">
            <li>Advanced Methods module (qualitative, quantitative, or mixed)</li>
            <li>Data collection in professional context</li>
            <li>Data analysis and interpretation</li>
            <li>Annual review milestone (written submission and viva)</li>
            <li>Emerging findings seminar (peer presentation)</li>
            <li>Monthly supervision meetings</li>
            <li>Two residential weekends</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <div class="text-xl font-bold text-accent mb-3">Year 3</div>
          <h3 class="font-semibold mb-3">Writing &amp; Submission</h3>
          <ul class="text-muted text-sm space-y-2">
            <li>Thesis writing and supervisor feedback cycles</li>
            <li>Academic Writing for Doctoral Research module</li>
            <li>Pre-submission review (faculty panel feedback)</li>
            <li>Thesis submission</li>
            <li>Viva voce examination</li>
            <li>Minor or major corrections (if required)</li>
            <li>Award of DBA</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Supervision -->
  <section class="py-16 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
      <p class="section-label mb-3">Supervision</p>
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6">Expert, Committed Supervision</h2>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
        <div>
          <p class="text-muted mb-4">Every DBA researcher has both a primary supervisor and a second supervisor. Your primary supervisor holds expertise in your research area and provides the central intellectual guidance for your thesis. Your second supervisor brings methodological expertise and provides continuity and a second perspective.</p>
          <p class="text-muted mb-4">You meet formally with your supervisor team a minimum of eight times per year, with all meetings logged on our online platform. Informal contact between meetings is encouraged and normal.</p>
          <p class="text-muted">Supervisor allocation is based on careful matching between your research interests and supervisor expertise. The Academic Lead for Research &amp; Enterprise leads this process before you enrol.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="space-y-3">
          <div class="card">
            <p class="text-sm text-muted"><strong class="text-foreground">Primary supervisor:</strong> Expert in your research area. Minimum 4 meetings per year plus informal contact.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="card">
            <p class="text-sm text-muted"><strong class="text-foreground">Second supervisor:</strong> Methodological specialist. Minimum 4 meetings per year, plus joint supervision meetings.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="card">
            <p class="text-sm text-muted"><strong class="text-foreground">Annual Review:</strong> Formal milestone assessment each year, including written submission and oral discussion with a panel including your supervisor and an independent faculty member.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="bg-surface border-t border-border py-16 px-6 text-center">
    <div class="max-w-2xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4">Ready to apply?</h2>
      <p class="text-muted mb-8">The first step is a conversation. Our admissions team will help you assess whether the DBA is the right fit for your research interests and professional context.</p>
      <div class="flex gap-4 justify-center flex-wrap">
        <a href="/apply" class="btn-primary">Start your application</a>
        <a href="/connect" class="btn-outline">Book a conversation</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>
